beer.beer_description: It may be the calm before the storm, but no one can deny the beer climate is changing. Season(al)s are creeping, traditional styles are melting down, and storm clouds are rolling in. Sounds like it’s time for an updated formulation — a different sort of winter warmer for a changing globe. A cloudy, unfiltered, hop-intensified Global Warmer should do the trick. Or, we could kid ourselves and deny the whole thing…

items.badge_description: The battle for grid iron supremacy is on. Who will be the victor? Who are we kidding, with your favorite brew and this badge, you've already won!

Get out there and raise a ruckus with your favorite Amber or Red Ale! That is 30 different beers with the style of American Amber / Red Ale, American Amber / Red Lager, Irish Red Ale or Imperial / Double Red Ale. Try 5 more for Level 7!

When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 115 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 24!
